sources.connection:
The open problem asks whether the minimal achievable all-time regret \(\mathcal R^*(G)\) must grow with the number of types \(n\) (or under what conditions). This citing work is directly about achieving constant (all-time) regret, but in a more general “multi-way” matching model and via a primal-dual method.

However, with only the title and abstract, we cannot determine:
- whether their constant-regret guarantee applies to the two-way setting of the open problem under comparable assumptions;
- whether the regret bound’s constant is independent of \(n\) (which would strongly inform the open problem), or instead scales with \(n\), \(|M|\), or other instance parameters;
- whether they provide lower bounds showing necessary dependence on \(n\).

Thus, the paper appears to provide partial progress/related evidence: it suggests constant-regret policies exist (possibly with improved dependence), but it does not, from available information, resolve whether \(\mathcal R^*(G)\) must grow with \(n\).

